summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions on terrorism, 
Expressing determination to facilitate counter-terrorism obligations,
Reaffirming resolution 1373 (2001) and supporting international efforts against terrorism,
Acting under Chapter VII of the UN Charter,

1. Decides exemptions to financial sanctions for:
   (a) Basic expenses (food, rent, medicine, taxes etc.) with Committee notification and no objection within 48 hours;
   (b) Extraordinary expenses, subject to Committee approval;

2. Allows addition to frozen accounts of:
   (a) Interest and earnings;
   (b) Payments due under pre-existing contracts;

3. Directs the Committee to:
   (a) Maintain a list of States notifying intent to apply exemptions;
   (b) Approve requests for extraordinary expenses;

4. Terminates the exception in resolution 1267 (1999);

5. Urges consideration of these points in implementing resolution 1373 (2001);

6. Remains seized of the matter.
